<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>He was given the difficult task of informing Locky Gilbert and Irena Srbinovska that they couldn't travel to Victoria for their hometown date due to the State's escalating coronavirus situation.</p>

<p>And viewers on Wednesday night's episode of The Bachelor were left fascinated by Osher Günsberg's pronunciation of the deadly virus, COVID-19.</p>

<p>Fans couldn't resist rushing to Twitter to mock his delivery of the word, with some admitting that he had managed to make the unpleasant word sound 'fancy'.</p>

<p>Scroll down for video</p>

<p>'What did he just say?' Viewers on Wednesday night's episode of The Bachelor were left fascinated by Osher Günsberg's pronunciation of the deadly virus, COVID-19</p>

<p>Osher was seen interrupting Locky and Irena's smitten date by telling them: 'The COVID situation in Melbourne has degraded significantly since you came back to the mansion.</p>

<p>'Now all of Melbourne is back in lockdown, and they have closed the border between New South Wales and Victoria.'</p>

<p>While a devastated Irena and Locky hugged and figured out their next course of action, viewers at home were amused by the way Osher's had pronounced the lethal respiratory virus.</p>

<p>One said: 'Anyone going to talk about how "osher gunsberg just pronounced covid #TheBachelorAU.'</p>

